<paragraph id="3E7636CA9C33FF898E10155EFCF9FC83" blockId="1.[340,860,791,818]" box="[340,860,791,818]" pageId="1" pageNumber="196">
<heading id="653E81A69C33FF898E10155EFCF9FC83" bold="true" box="[340,860,791,818]" centered="true" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="1" pageNumber="196" reason="2">
<emphasis id="0CBDEAD89C33FF898E10155EFCF9FC83" bold="true" box="[340,860,791,818]" pageId="1" pageNumber="196">
The genera 
<taxonomicName id="F9C94D499C33FF898EAB155EFDDBFC83" authorityName="Mac Leay" authorityYear="1827" box="[495,638,792,818]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Megamerus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="196" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="0CBDEAD89C33FF898EAB155EFDDBFC83" bold="true" box="[495,638,792,818]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="196">Megamerus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="F9C94D499C33FF898D801551FCF9FC83" authorityName="Chapuis" authorityYear="1878" box="[708,860,791,818]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Rhagiosoma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="196" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="0CBDEAD89C33FF898D801551FCF9FC83" bold="true" box="[708,860,791,818]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="196">Rhagiosoma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="76D365419C33FF898FCA1516FE22FAD9" pageId="1" pageNumber="196" type="description">
<paragraph id="3E7636CA9C33FF898FCA1516FD16FC39" blockId="1.[112,1088,848,1385]" pageId="1" pageNumber="196">
Externally, 
<taxonomicName id="F9C94D499C33FF898E4C1514FE28FCD8" authorityName="Chapuis" authorityYear="1878" box="[264,397,850,873]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Rhagiosoma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="196" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="0CBDEAD89C33FF898E4C1514FE28FCD8" box="[264,397,850,873]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="196">Rhagiosoma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="F9C94D499C33FF898E851514FD9AFCD8" authorityName="Mac Leay" authorityYear="1827" box="[449,575,850,873]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Megamerus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="196" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="0CBDEAD89C33FF898E851514FD9AFCD8" box="[449,575,850,873]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="196">Megamerus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have a similar shape of body outline and should be distinguished by characters summarized in 
<tableCitation id="734B03719C33FF898D191536FD09FC39" box="[605,684,880,904]" captionStart="Table 1" captionStartId="2.[151,198,219,238]" captionText="Table 1. Differential characters of genera Rhagiosoma Chapuis, 1878, and Megamerus MacLeay, 1827." pageId="1" pageNumber="196">Table 1</tableCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="3E7636CA9C33FF898FCA15D4FE22FAD9" blockId="1.[112,1088,848,1385]" pageId="1" pageNumber="196">
<taxonomicName id="F9C94D499C33FF898FCA15D4FEA9FC18" authorityName="Mac Leay" authorityYear="1827" box="[142,268,914,937]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Megamerus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="196" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="0CBDEAD89C33FF898FCA15D4FEA9FC18" box="[142,268,914,937]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="196">Megamerus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="F9C94D499C33FF898E7B15D4FE61FC18" authorityName="Chapuis" authorityYear="1878" box="[319,452,914,937]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Rhagiosoma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="196" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="0CBDEAD89C33FF898E7B15D4FE61FC18" box="[319,452,914,937]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="196">Rhagiosoma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
also differ in the shape of male genitalia; this character was not studied by 
<bibRefCitation id="5A584B3B9C33FF898E5215F7FE64FC79" author="MONROS F." box="[278,449,944,968]" pageId="1" pageNumber="196" pagination="104 - 115" refId="ref4284" refString="MONROS F. 1956: Sur le genere Megamerus MacLeay (Col. Chrysomelidae). Revue Francaise d'Entomologie 23: 104 - 115." type="journal article" year="1956">MONRÓS (1956)</bibRefCitation>
. I have examined male genitalia of 
<typeStatus id="E17288689C33FF898C0B15F7FCD8FC78" box="[847,893,945,969]" pageId="1" pageNumber="196">type</typeStatus>
specimens of the following species: 
<taxonomicName id="F9C94D499C33FF898E7A1594FE12FC58" authorityName="Sekerka" authorityYear="2007" box="[318,439,978,1001]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Rhagiosoma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="196" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chapuisi" status="nom. nov.">
<emphasis id="0CBDEAD89C33FF898E7A1594FE12FC58" box="[318,439,978,1001]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="196">R. chapuisi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="178E57A39C33FF898E851597FD95FC59" box="[449,560,977,1000]" pageId="1" pageNumber="196">nom. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, 
<taxonomicName id="F9C94D499C33FF898D781594FD62FC58" authorityName="Duvivier" authorityYear="1891" box="[572,711,978,1001]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Rhagiosoma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="196" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fraternum">
<emphasis id="0CBDEAD89C33FF898D781594FD62FC58" box="[572,711,978,1001]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="196">R. fraternum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="F9C94D499C33FF898D921594FCEAFC58" authorityName="Reineck" authorityYear="1913" box="[726,847,978,1001]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Rhagiosoma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="196" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="grossum">
<emphasis id="0CBDEAD89C33FF898D921594FCEAFC58" box="[726,847,978,1001]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="196">R. grossum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="F9C94D499C33FF898C1B1594FB9AFC58" authorityName="Heyden" authorityYear="1877" box="[863,1087,978,1001]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Mecynodera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="196" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="madagascariensis">
<emphasis id="0CBDEAD89C33FF898C1B1594FB9AFC58" box="[863,1087,978,1001]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="196">R. madagascariensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and four other unidentified Madagascan species. I have also seen specimens of 
<taxonomicName id="F9C94D499C33FF898C8515B4FEF4FB99" authority="MacLeay, 1827" authorityName="MacLeay" authorityYear="1827" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Megamerus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="196" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kingi">
<emphasis id="0CBDEAD89C33FF898C8515B4FF00FB98" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="196">Megamerus kingi</emphasis>
MacLeay, 1827
</taxonomicName>
(
<typeStatus id="E17288689C33FF898E241256FE2AFB99" box="[352,399,1040,1064]" pageId="1" pageNumber="196">type</typeStatus>
species of 
<taxonomicName id="F9C94D499C33FF898D431254FD20FB98" authorityName="Mac Leay" authorityYear="1827" box="[519,645,1042,1065]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Megamerus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="196" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="0CBDEAD89C33FF898D431254FD20FB98" box="[519,645,1042,1065]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="196">Megamerus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), and 
<emphasis id="0CBDEAD89C33FF898D8C1254FD43FB98" box="[712,742,1042,1065]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="196">M.</emphasis>
cf. 
<emphasis id="0CBDEAD89C33FF898C4A1254FCD6FB98" box="[782,883,1042,1065]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="196">femoralis</emphasis>
Lea, 1917. I found strong differences in the shape of the parameres and aedeagus. In 
<taxonomicName id="F9C94D499C33FF898C651274FC3AFBF8" authorityName="Mac Leay" authorityYear="1827" box="[801,927,1074,1097]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Megamerus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="196" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="0CBDEAD89C33FF898C651274FC3AFBF8" box="[801,927,1074,1097]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="196">Megamerus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the parameres are robust and gradually thickened towards apex, with a shallow apical cleft and apex of each face broadly rounded (
<figureCitation id="A6F22A4F9C33FF898ED21236FE44FB39" box="[406,481,1136,1160]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="4.[152,191,1578,1597]" captionTargetBox="[186,1091,448,1551]" captionTargetId="figure-10@4.[185,1092,447,1551]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Figs. 1-3. 1 – Megamerus kingi MacLeay, 1827; 2 – Rhagiosoma madagascariense (Heyden, 1877); 3 – R. chapuisi nom. nov.; a – aedeagus, dorsal view; b – aedeagus, lateral view; c – parameres, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5328317" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5328317/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="196">Fig. 1c</figureCitation>
), this structure is rather similar to 
<taxonomicName id="F9C94D499C33FF898C091234FB99FB39" authority="Fabricius, 1792" authorityName="Fabricius" authorityYear="1792" box="[845,1084,1136,1161]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Sagra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="196" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="0CBDEAD89C33FF898C091234FC28FB38" box="[845,909,1138,1161]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="196">Sagra</emphasis>
Fabricius, 1792
</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName id="F9C94D499C33FF898F3412D4FF50FB18" authorityName="Chapuis" authorityYear="1878" box="[112,245,1170,1193]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Rhagiosoma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="196" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="0CBDEAD89C33FF898F3412D4FF50FB18" box="[112,245,1170,1193]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="196">Rhagiosoma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have apices of parameres not thickened but with a very deep apical cleft (often reaching to 2/3 of length) and each apical face angulate to slightly obtuse (
<figureCitation id="A6F22A4F9C33FF898CC112F6FBA6FB79" box="[901,1027,1200,1224]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="4.[152,191,1578,1597]" captionTargetBox="[186,1091,448,1551]" captionTargetId="figure-10@4.[185,1092,447,1551]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Figs. 1-3. 1 – Megamerus kingi MacLeay, 1827; 2 – Rhagiosoma madagascariense (Heyden, 1877); 3 – R. chapuisi nom. nov.; a – aedeagus, dorsal view; b – aedeagus, lateral view; c – parameres, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5328317" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5328317/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="196">Figs. 2c, 3c</figureCitation>
). The aedeagus in 
<taxonomicName id="F9C94D499C33FF898FB51294FECAFB58" authorityName="Mac Leay" authorityYear="1827" box="[241,367,1234,1257]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Megamerus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="196" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="0CBDEAD89C33FF898FB51294FECAFB58" box="[241,367,1234,1257]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="196">Megamerus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is very stout, parallel-sided, without a sharp apex and with a shallow apical cleft (
<figureCitation id="A6F22A4F9C33FF898FB212B6FEC7FAB9" box="[246,354,1264,1288]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="4.[152,191,1578,1597]" captionTargetBox="[186,1091,448,1551]" captionTargetId="figure-10@4.[185,1092,447,1551]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Figs. 1-3. 1 – Megamerus kingi MacLeay, 1827; 2 – Rhagiosoma madagascariense (Heyden, 1877); 3 – R. chapuisi nom. nov.; a – aedeagus, dorsal view; b – aedeagus, lateral view; c – parameres, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5328317" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5328317/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="196">Figs. 1a,b</figureCitation>
). On the other hand, 
<taxonomicName id="F9C94D499C33FF898D0C12B4FD68FAB8" authorityName="Chapuis" authorityYear="1878" box="[584,717,1266,1289]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Rhagiosoma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="196" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="0CBDEAD89C33FF898D0C12B4FD68FAB8" box="[584,717,1266,1289]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="196">Rhagiosoma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has the aedeagus parallel-sided in the anterior part and then tapered; the apex is sharp and differently shaped than in 
<taxonomicName id="F9C94D499C33FF898C9E1354FF37FAF8" authorityName="Mac Leay" authorityYear="1827" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Megamerus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="196" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="0CBDEAD89C33FF898C9E1354FF37FAF8" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="196">Megamerus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation id="A6F22A4F9C33FF898FE61376FE87FAF9" box="[162,290,1328,1352]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="4.[152,191,1578,1597]" captionTargetBox="[186,1091,448,1551]" captionTargetId="figure-10@4.[185,1092,447,1551]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Figs. 1-3. 1 – Megamerus kingi MacLeay, 1827; 2 – Rhagiosoma madagascariense (Heyden, 1877); 3 – R. chapuisi nom. nov.; a – aedeagus, dorsal view; b – aedeagus, lateral view; c – parameres, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5328317" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5328317/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="196">Figs. 2a, 3a</figureCitation>
). The findings mentioned above lead me to remove 
<taxonomicName id="F9C94D499C33FF898C121374FC7EFAF8" authorityName="Chapuis" authorityYear="1878" box="[854,987,1330,1353]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Rhagiosoma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="196" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="0CBDEAD89C33FF898C121374FC7EFAF8" box="[854,987,1330,1353]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="196">Rhagiosoma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from the synonymy of 
<taxonomicName id="F9C94D499C33FF898E471314FE24FAD8" authorityName="Mac Leay" authorityYear="1827" box="[259,385,1362,1385]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Megamerus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="196" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="0CBDEAD89C33FF898E471314FE24FAD8" box="[259,385,1362,1385]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="196">Megamerus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
